text:
146th Street. north from Rockaway Boulevard, showing two rows of newly erected homes. The two rows are on either side of 146th Street and the Boulevard is in the foreground. The sign on the left reads: ,250 down will secure one of these beautiful homes--6 rooms and sun porch-- tiled kitchen, built-in bathtub, pedestal basin, stairway to attic-- Breakfast Nook furnished, Ironing Board-Beautiful Electric Fixtures-- Parquet Floors-- Steam and Hot Wnter-Sewers in Street.
The plots facing on Rockaway Boulevard are reserved for business
buildings.
P. L. Sperr  March 15, 1927
